 WHAT THE SERVER SEES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 For a victim who is CFG.Size (9–14) studs away in real space:
   • Attacker position  : real, server-side accurate
   • Victim position    : real (server owns it, drag was local-only)
   • Kill distance      : 9–14 studs (the real, un-dragged distance)
   • Kill angle         : real angle (we enforce AngleCap pre-drag)
   • RemoteEvent timing : spaced by DragCooldown (0.40 s)
   • No BreakJoints     : no joint anomaly event
   • No position delta  : server never saw victim move

 The only detectable signal is:
   1. Kill distances slightly elevated vs true melee range
   2. RemoteEvent fires at a consistent rate just under the burst limit
   3. Kills register at the edge of "plausible" range, consistently
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
--]]
